comments[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-16T05:50:52.543Z",maintainer-agent,"Duplicate check: searched all-status for 'deps context missing count enumerate', 'missing_count', 'graph context missing references' — only pm-p9sc (closed, inverse defect), pm-8xr8 (consumer story), pm-2ler (closed classification precedent). No open owner; registry consulted."
  "2026-07-17T06:12:22.519Z",maintainer-agent,"Fix evidence 2026-07-17: context format missing_count was workspace-global (counted every dangling target in the tracker) while tree counted traversal-encountered missing nodes - the pm-96h7 3-vs-0 contradiction. Now missing_count is traversal-scoped (missing nodes reachable under the same direction/kinds/max-depth that built the packet, independent of node/token pagination so it is stable across cursor pages), missing_scope:\"traversal\" documents the semantics in the payload, missing_reference_count totals the dangling declarations inside the packet, and missing_references enumerates bounded rows (holder_id, target_id, kind, source, holder_status, legacy_terminal) reusing the pm-2ler active/legacy split so agents can tell repairable typos from historical debt. no-active-blocker sentinels are excluded. Tree agreement verified in spec and in a packed-tarball E2E (tree missing:1 == context missing_count:1 on the same root/depth). Covering specs: deps-command.spec.ts (enumeration, bounding via --edge-limit, direction scoping, legacy classification on closed holders, sentinel skip via raw legacy fixture)."
  "2026-07-17T06:16:03.410Z",codex-root,"Handoff accepted by codex-root: preserving the existing graph-context implementation and completing exact coverage, quality gates, temp-package proof, review convergence, merge, and merged-head verification."
  "2026-07-17T06:27:05.189Z",maintainer-agent,"Final verification: linked sandbox test passed; focused graph/CLI surface passed 140 tests; full literal all-source coverage passed 296 files / 5,767 tests at exact 100/100/100/100; lint found zero warnings and zero clones; static quality/docstrings/package boundary/token budget/typecheck/contracts/docs/secret gates passed; packed @unbrained/pm-cli consumer proved tree/context missing_count parity, bounded enumeration/classification, direction/kind filtering, and cursor continuation."
  "2026-07-17T06:47:05.278Z",maintainer-agent,"Greptile pre-push review 87d5938f (4/5, no correctness defects): accepted all three maintainability suggestions. Deps now parses direction/kinds/depth/bounds once and shares the typed options between packet assembly and missing closure; public docs/help state that --edge-limit also caps missing_references while missing_reference_count preserves the total; BFS queue now has an explicit minimal id/distance type. Focused build, 124 tests, ESLint, typecheck, and contract snapshot passed."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-17T06:12:41.039Z",maintainer-agent,"When two output formats disagree on a count, scope the count to the traversal that produced the payload and stamp the scope into the payload (missing_scope) - agreement claims in docs alone rot; a self-describing field survives format evolution. Computing the missing set from an unbounded-closure over the same direction/kinds/depth (ignoring node/token pagination) keeps the count stable across cursor pages."
